Class MetadataFinder

com.conceptwave.scripting.Object

public class MetadataFinder
extends CwMetadataObject

Finders are used for searching, accessing, adding, updating and deleting data from different data sources such as databases and external systems. Information that is returned by the Finder object is displayed using the Finder User Interface. Contained within the Finder User Interface are several Forms that enable you to customize the display of the data at runtime.

selectInputDocument

public CwMetadataObject selectInputDocument
READONLY: It is required when the Finder needs search criteria for the select operation. When used in the UI, the Finder search criteria are entered using the form specified in the Search Form field of the Finder's View tab.

selectOutputDocument

public CwMetadataObject selectOutputDocument
READONLY: Finders must always define a Select output Document. The result of the Finder select operation is a list of runtime Select output Document instances that contain the data matching the search criteria. When used in the User Interface, the Finder results are displayed using the form specified in the Result Form field of the Finder's Views tab.

views

public MetadataFinderView[] views
READONLY: A view specifies one distinctive way to represent a Finder in the User Interface. Each view is defined by the Finder Result Form specified in the view.
